  "description": [
    "Friday April 2 1954 The American Moses BY DAVID SCHWARTZ Copyright 1954 Jewish Telegraphic Agency Inc April has the birthdays of a few celebrities but it is the month of the birthday of the man whom Henry Adams once described as the Moses of democracyThomas Jefferson Not much of a fuss id made over Jeffersons birthday In a sense he needs none July 4ih is really his memorial During his life Jefferson to avoid celebrations of his birthday refused to divulge the day of his birth Jefferson wasnt particularly good looking He was often mis taken for a farmerit was said he got better looking as he grew older He was the common man At the time of his election to the Presidency he lived a Wash ington boarding house and even on the morning of his inaugura tion refused to take a seat at the head of the table He walked to the Capitol to be sworn in At the White House functions dur ing his Presidency protocol was dropped An ambassador or a minister sat down where the seat was empty irrespective of his status A common man he was the most uncommon man He was an able"
  ],
